The term '''city fathers''' (or '''stadtväter''') is used to mean two things: firstly (and most commonly), it denotes a member of a municipal council over a city. Secondly, it can signify the "[[Founding Fathers]]" of the city.

In this sense, city fathers are usually those men (and once in a while, women) who founded the city and/or its major institutions.

==City Fathers==

* One notable example from [[fiction]] is [[List_of_recurring_characters_from_The_Simpsons#Jebediah_Springfield|Jebediah Springfield]], from ''[[The Simpsons]].''

* In ''[[A Series of Unfortunate Events]]'', by [[Lemony Snicket]], the [[Council of Elders (A Series of Unfortunate Events)|Council of Elders]] is an example of city fathers.

* The Daley family of [[Chicago]] could be an example of city fathers from the present-day.

